# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Output of the go coverage tool, specifically when used with LiteIDE
*.out

# go mod vendor output — used as a manual escape hatch when the eu10
# stager can't download the dep tree in time; not committed. Decide per
# fork whether to commit it (reproducible deploys without network) or
# keep regenerating (leaner repo).
vendor/

# Cross-compiled binary produced for `cf push -b binary_buildpack -c
# './bin/server'`. The deploy workflow writes it on the runner; a
# manual laptop-side cross-compile (see README §4 escape hatch) writes
# the same path locally. Never committed.
bin/

# Local CF-push variables (copied from vars.example.yml, holds per-deploy values)
vars.yml

# Local service-binding dumps used to run the app off-platform. `cf env`
# / VCAP_SERVICES copied into one of these holds the XSUAA, Destination,
# and Connectivity client secrets in cleartext — never commit them.
default-env.json
.env
*.env

# Claude Code session-management / local-settings tooling. Not sensitive
# today, but the directory's contents are evolving and should never be
# accidentally staged via `git add -A`.
.claude/

# Node.js dependencies — installed by `npm ci` in CI and `npm install`
# locally for prettier. Never committed.
node_modules/
